  </row>
</tabular>
</statement>
<exercise workspace="0.01in">
    <introduction>
        <p>
        Let <m>t</m> be the trial number (input), and <m>r</m> be the number remaining (output).  Construct a scattergram in Desmos and make a rough sketch below.  Do not forget your labels.  Let your window (see the wrench on the right side) be <m>-5 &lt; x &lt; 50</m> and <m>-5 &lt; y &lt; 10</m>.
      </p>
    </introduction>
</exercise>
<exercise workspace="0.01in">
    <introduction>
        <p>
        Which type of function, linear or exponential, do you think best models the data?  Why?
        </p>
    </introduction>
</exercise>
<exercise>
